 oaks and ashes than in other tree species. Roost switching rate was associated with ambient temperature and tree species selected by the bats. The bats changed roosts more frequently when the minimum ambient temperature increased, and less often in ashes than in oaks and other tree species. Our results show that bat group size and roost switching behaviour are shaped by both environmental factors and the stage of reproduction.", "access_right": "restricted", "creators": [{"name": "Ruczy\u0144ski, Ireneusz", "affiliation": null}, {"name": "Barto\u0144, Kamil A.", "affiliation": null}], "keywords": ["Biodiversity", "Mammalia", "Chiroptera", "Chordata", "Animalia", "bats", "bat"], "related_identifiers": [{"identifier": "hash://md5/7ba394fa047cba05788b8178ae97e6a7", "relation": "hasVersion", "scheme": "url"}, {"identifier": "hash://sha256/785fb3fd8098b96c2e0b55a4487c612718062f22a663c476cc32f1619496d91d", "relation": "hasVersion", "scheme": "url"}, {"identifier": "zotero://select/groups/5435545/items/LUMVZAC7", "relation": "isDerivedFrom", "scheme": "url"}, {"identifier": "https://zotero.org/groups/5435545/items/LUMVZAC7", "relation": "isDerivedFrom", "scheme": "url"}, {"identifier": "https://linker.bio/cut:hash://md5/c79c4bee60392bd98cfdb3c45261f5d2!/b270219-272709", "relation": "isDerivedFrom", "scheme": "url"}, {"identifier": "hash://md5/ce1e7618f237ff56e74d51f496e811a3", "relation": "isPartOf", "scheme": "url"}, {"identifier": "10.5281/zenodo.1410543", "relation": "isCompiledBy", "resource_type": "software", "scheme": "doi"}], "custom": {"dwc:class": ["Mammalia"], "dwc:kingdom": ["Animalia"], "dwc:order": ["Chiroptera"], "dwc:phylum": ["Chordata"]}, "resource_type": {"title": "Journal article", "type": "publication", "subtype": "article"}, "journal": {"issue": "5", "pages": "63", "title": "Behavioral Ecology and Sociobiology", "volume": "74"}, "alternate_identifiers": [{"identifier": "hash://md5/7ba394fa047cba05788b8178ae97e6a7"}, {"identifier": "urn:lsid:zotero.org